vendored_by_commit: AUD-406 follow-up (codeload setup-node flake on PR #169)
notes: |
  NOT a verbatim copy of upstream action.yml.

  Rationale: actions/setup-node is `using: node20` — its real surface is a
  multi-MB compiled dist/index.js (Node distribution download, tool-cache
  management, actions/cache integration). Copying only its action.yml does not
  work, and vendoring the JS bundle is large, opaque, and defeats the AUD-406
  auditability goal. On these [self-hosted, linux] runners Node 20 + npm are
  already provisioned (Volta), so setup-node installs nothing here — its only
  effective jobs were "node on PATH" (already true) and `cache: "npm"`
  (redundant: the persistent runner reuses ~/.npm natively across jobs).

  This composite therefore ASSERTS the runner toolchain in pure bash instead
  of fetching the upstream JS action from codeload.github.com. It eliminates
  both the setup-node fetch AND the implied actions/cache fetch from the
  critical path. Input surface (node-version, cache) is kept drop-in
  compatible so ci.yml `with:` blocks are unchanged.

  Re-evaluate / revert procedure:
    - If a runner stops pre-provisioning Node (assertion fails fast with a
      clear ::error::), either restore Volta provisioning on the runner OR
      reintroduce a vendored real installer.
    - To re-pin upstream instead: revert ci.yml `uses: ./.github/actions/setup-node`
      back to `actions/setup-node@<new-sha> # pin vN (AUD-406)` and delete
      this directory.
  scope: |
    Applied to .github/workflows/ci.yml only (the workflow whose PR #169 run
    hit the codeload timeout). Other workflows still use upstream
    actions/setup-node; npm-publish.yml notably needs setup-node's
    registry-url auth, which this assertion shim intentionally does not cover.
